.TH GODOT-TUI 1 "July 2026" "godot-tui" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
godot-tui \- keyboard-first terminal interface for Godot 4 projects
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B godot-tui
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ project-directory ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B godot-tui
opens a Godot 4 project in a Bubble Tea terminal interface. With no project
argument it opens the current working directory. The project argument may be a
directory or a project.godot file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "-p, --project " PATH
Open PATH as a project. PATH may be a project directory or project.godot.
.TP
.B "-h, --help"
Display command-line help.
.TP
.B "-v, --version"
Display the build version and injected commit.
.TP
.B --config
Print the active platform-specific configuration path.
.TP
.B --ensure-config
Create the default configuration file if it does not exist, then exit.
.SH TUI KEYS
.TP
.B r
Run the selected scene.
.TP
.B b
Build/import the project.
.TP
.B l
Open live Godot output.
.TP
.B [ / ]
Cycle the live performance metric view in the bottom dashboard panel while a
run is active.
.TP
.B o
Open godot.toml in the configured editor and reload it after the editor exits.
.TP
.B q
Quit the interface.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/delbysoft/godot.toml
Linux configuration path. macOS and Windows use os.UserConfigDir platform
locations.
.TP
.I ~/.config/delbysoft/godot-tui/sessions/
Default Linux debug session history directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR godot (1)
.SH AUTHOR
delbysoft
